section.section:
"Account" includes:
Checking and other demand deposit accounts;
Negotiable order of withdrawal and other savings accounts;
Share draft accounts; and
Certificated and uncertificated time deposit accounts.

"Multiple-party account" does not include any:
Account established and designated for the deposit of funds of a corporation, partnership, joint venture, limited liability company, or other association of persons for business purposes;
Account established and designated for the deposit of funds of a charitable or civic organization;
Fiduciary account where the relationship is established other than by the account agreement;
Account established and designated as governed under the Maryland Uniform Transfers to Minors Act;
Account established and designated as governed under Title 13, Subtitle 4 of the Estates and Trusts Article; or
Account that would not be a multiple-party account except for the fact that 1 or more convenience persons are authorized to draw upon funds in the account.
